---
description: Next.js frontend conventions.
globs: frontend/**
alwaysApply: false
---

- TypeScript strict mode, no any. Share contract types with the backend.
- Server Components by default; Client Components only when interactivity requires it.
- Use TanStack Query for all server state. No ad hoc fetching inside useEffect.
- Validate all forms with Zod.
- Use shadcn/ui components; keep them small and accessible (labels, keyboard nav, focus states).
- Uploads go directly to S3 via a presigned URL requested from the backend.
- No secrets in client code; only expose public environment variables.
